        <StackPanel
            Margin="0,30,0,0"
            VerticalAlignment="Center"
            DockPanel.Dock="Top"
            Orientation="Horizontal">
            <TextBlock VerticalAlignment="Center" FontSize="28">“I just read a few words to you for your memory. Please try to recall them and tell me what these words are all about?”</TextBlock>
            <ContentControl
                Margin="10,0,0,0"
                HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                VerticalAlignment="Center"
                ContentTemplate="{StaticResource MMSE_MoCA_ToolTipTemplate}">
                <ContentControl.Content>
                    <TextBlock TextTrimming="CharacterEllipsis" TextWrapping="Wrap">
                        Rating: After delaying free recollection, patients are encouraged to recall words that cannot be recalled through semantic classification cues. After the classification prompts to be a multiple-choice prompt, the correct one should be recalled, and then type in the corresponding empty column.（√）As a mark. First make a classification prompt. If you still cannot recall it, then make a multi-select prompt. For example:“Which of the following words is just recorded: nose, face, palm?”
                    </TextBlock>
                </ContentControl.Content>
            </ContentControl>
            <Button
                Width="51"
                Height="36"
                Background="Transparent"
                BorderBrush="Transparent"
                Click="ExecuteAudioPlayClick"
                Cursor="Hand"
                Tag="I just read a few words to you for your memory. Please try to recall them and tell me what these words are.">
                <Button.Content>
                    <Image
                        Width="28"
                        Height="24"
                        VerticalAlignment="Center"
                        Cursor="Hand"
                        Source="{StaticResource crs_sound}"
                        Stretch="Uniform" />
                </Button.Content>
            </Button>
        </StackPanel>
